<span id="freeTextContainer9811451972714422513">Moving slowly yest steadily with the series. <br/>I think this book was most subdued and quiet, mailny due to the location - a monastery - and a small group of monks, vowed to remain silent. At the centre of this beautiful mystery are Gregorian chants, and Ms Penny masterfully presents the idea behind them. That was a real treat although not that easy for me to follow.<br/></span>

