<span id="freeTextContainer14671775404594010650">This might&apos;ve been the fastest I&apos;ve finished a Louise Penny, but luckily I thought the eighth entry in the Gamache series just kept on getting better and better! I&apos;ll keep these reviews short because there&apos;s nothing that I say that probably hasn&apos;t been said a bunch of times before, but they all are so perfectly campy in a way that also doesn&apos;t feel like a cozy mystery. Both complicated and dark yet light-hearted. Compared to the rest of the series this is in my top three or four. </span>
  <span id="freeText14671775404594010650" style="display:none">This might've been the fastest I've finished a Louise Penny, but luckily I thought the eighth entry in the Gamache series just kept on getting better and better! I'll keep these reviews short because there's nothing that I say that probably hasn't been said a bunch of times before, but they all are so perfectly campy in a way that also doesn't feel like a cozy mystery. Both complicated and dark yet light-hearted. Compared to the rest of the series this is in my top three or four. </span>
