<div id="review_1693385081" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1693385081" />
    <a title="Kathleen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/39134508-kathleen"><img alt="Kathleen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1495314753p2/39134508.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1693385081?book_show_action=true">Sep 19, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathleen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathleen" href="/user/show/39134508-kathleen">Kathleen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9781427226105" href="/book/show/33651792-the-beautiful-mystery">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=canadian-author">canadian-author</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=canadian-bingo-2020">canadian-bingo-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=suspense">suspense</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=2020">2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=4-star-books">4-star-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=canadian-literature">canadian-literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=crime-fiction">crime-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1693385081" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11380909462820084495">&quot;And a man&apos;s foes,&quot; she read out loud, &quot;shall be they of his own household.&quot; <br/>Matthew 10:36<br/><br/>The Beautiful Mystery #8 in A Chief Inspector Gamache series by Louise Penny is a haunting and puzzling mystery. I listened to the audio version of this book. <br/>Captain Charbonneau, who ran the Surete du Quebec station in La Maurice, met Chief Inspector Armand Gamache and Inspector Jean-Guy Beauvoir at the plane and drove them to the dock, and after a twenty-minute boat ride on the remote lake in the wilderne</span>
  <span id="freeText11380909462820084495" style="display:none">"And a man's foes," she read out loud, "shall be they of his own household." <br />Matthew 10:36<br /><br />The Beautiful Mystery #8 in A Chief Inspector Gamache series by Louise Penny is a haunting and puzzling mystery. I listened to the audio version of this book. <br />Captain Charbonneau, who ran the Surete du Quebec station in La Maurice, met Chief Inspector Armand Gamache and Inspector Jean-Guy Beauvoir at the plane and drove them to the dock, and after a twenty-minute boat ride on the remote lake in the wilderness of Quebec they arrived at the near mythical monastery of Saint-Gilbert-Entre-les-Loups. Not a living soul except the twenty-four monks who lived there had ever been allowed to enter. <br /><br />Frere Luc had the key to open the huge wooden door to the outside world. He opened the door and led them into the monastery. <br />Earlier that morning, Dom Philippe, the abbot of Saint-Gilbert, called the police to report the murder of his prior. <br />Frere Mathieu, the prior and choirmaster at the monastery, was murdered. Inside a long black sleeve of his cassock was a rolled up sheet of sheepskin with Dies irae in Latin on it. Dies irae means 'day of wrath' and is from the Requiem Mass. <br />Is it the missing original Gregorian chant calligraphied many centuries ago? <br /><br />That evening the boatman takes Captain Charbonneau and Frere Mathieu's body back down the lake, while Gamache and Beauvoir stay behind. <br />"It's not threatening. It's just extreme peace."<br /><br />One of the twenty-three monks was responsible for the death of Frere Mathieu. But which one? <br /><br />Frere Simon, the abbot's secretary and gardener, found Frere Mathieu in the garden. Frere Simon's eyes never seemed to close. He watched everything and probably heard everything. <br />The abbot Dom Philippe strongly opposed the choirmaster Frere Mathieu's view about making a second recording of their Gregorian chants and making public appearances. The opposing views caused a chasm.<br /> Frere Charles, the doctor, claimed to be neutral in the debate about making a second recording of their chants. <br />Frere Antoine was the soloist on the recording and is now the new choir director. <br />Frere Bernard works with animals and works in the chocolate factory making delicious chocolate-covered blueberries. <br />Frere Raymond is in charge of maintenance and claims the foundation needs to be repaired, which will be extremely costly. <br /><br />Louise Penny writes multilevel stories with plots and subplots beneath the mystery. Chief Superintendent Francoeur shows up at the monastery disrupting the tranquility for Gamache and Beauvoir. <br />. <br />Ralph Cosham has the perfect voice for narrating this series. Each character has a distinct sounding voice, and the English and French accents seem genuine. I look forward to listening to Ralph Cosham narrate more of Penny's books.<br /><br />Although The Beautiful Mystery did not include The Three Pines and the quirky villagers, this novel captured and held my attention. I was very interested in Saint-Gilbert, the Masses, the monks, their lives and the chants. <br />I think that Frere Sebastien from the Congregation for the Doctrine of the Faith in Rome loves the beautiful chanting and will stay at Saint-Gilbert in the wilderness. But what will happen to Jean-Guy? <br /><br />Huge thanks to the Public Libraries, and the librarians who manage, organize and keep them running for the loan of this audiobook. <br />4.75</span>
  <a data-text-id="11380909462820084495" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


